    triangles = {}
    for i in lengths:
        area = i[0] * i[1]
        perimeter = i[0] + i[1] + i[2]
        if area not in triangles.keys():
            triangles[area] = [perimeter, i]
        else:
            if perimeter < triangles[area][0]:
                triangles[area] = [perimeter, i]
    
    # sort triangles by perimeter, ascending
    triangles = sorted(triangles.items(), key=lambda x: x[1][0])
    
    # calculate the min perimeter
    length = 0
    for i in triangles:
        length += i[1][0]
    
    return str(length)
